		<header2>How do I get help or submit a bug report?</header2>
		<body>
<!--
			The best way to submit a request for help or a bug report is to use the 
			<a href="http://electrotap.com/support/">Electrotap Support Form</a> on the Electrotap website.
			<br/><br/>
	
			You can also email <a href="mailto:support@electrotap.com">support@electrotap.com</a> with your question or comment.
			<br/><br/>
	
-->
			The easiest way to get help is to send an email to <a href="mailto:support@74objects.com">support@74objects.com</a>
			or to the <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/electrotap">Electrotap Google Group</a>.
			<br/><br/>
			
			It is of the utmost importance that you provide as much information as possible.  If the 
			report is ambiguous then it is very hard to help.  Here is a checklist of things we will be looking for:<br/><br/>
			<ul>
				<li>Platform: Mac OS 10.6.2 or Windows XP Service Pack 3 are two examples.</li>
				<li>Processor: Is this a PPC or an Intel processor?</li>
				<li>Crash Log: If you are on a Mac, please send the crash report!</li>
				<li>Max settings: Is overdrive turned on? What is you audio vector size and sample rate?</li>
				<li>Example Patch: If you can send a small patcher that demonstrates the problem, you will be much loved.</li>
				<li>Unambiguous steps to reproduce the problem.</li>
				<li>Registration number: believe it or not, this actually helps :-).</li>
				<li>Documentation List: What documentation have you read about the problem? Have you visited our <a href="http://electrotap.com/faqs">FAQ</a>?</li>
			</ul>
		</body>




